  "aiDescription": {
    "summary": "The \"Export Non-inventory part lines\" is a data export that retrieves non-inventory part lines from NetSuite sales orders. It is not configured to run in a sandbox environment. The export uses a NetSuite RESTlet as the source application, specifically the \"salesorder\" record type. It retrieves data using a saved search with the search ID \"1846\". The export also includes an expression transformation that extracts specific fields from the source data and generates new fields with the extracted values. The export is set to export data in batches of 100 records at a time.",
    "detailed": "This export is named \"Export Non-inventory part lines\" and it is not configured to run in a sandbox environment. \n\nThe export is using a NetSuite RESTlet as the source application. The RESTlet is configured to retrieve data from the \"salesorder\" record type in NetSuite. The export is using a saved search with the search ID \"1846\" to retrieve the data. The RESTlet version being used is \"suiteapp2.0\". \n\nThe export is also configured to transform the retrieved data using an expression transformation. The transformation includes a set of rules that extract specific fields from the source data and generate new fields with the extracted values. The rules extract fields such as \"id\", \"RecordType\", \"Order_Id\", \"line_ids\", \"Miva Shipment ID\", \"TrackingNum\", \"ShipCarrier\", and \"Internal ID\" from the source data. \n\nThe export is set to export data in batches of 100 records at a time. \n\nOverall, this export retrieves non-inventory part lines from NetSuite sales orders using a saved search and transforms the data by extracting specific fields and generating new fields based on the extracted values.",
